# 6. CI pipeline integration (GitHub Actions style)

```yaml id="ci-pipeline"
name: Microservices Audit

on:
  pull_request:
  schedule:
    - cron: "0 0 * * 1"

jobs:
  audit:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v3

      - name: Run audit collector
        run: python tools/generate_audit.py

      - name: Validate scores
        run: python tools/validate_audit.py

      - name: Fail if critical issues found
        run: python tools/gate_check.py
```

---

# 7. Domain-level aggregation

After per-service scoring:

```text
domain_score =
  average(service_scores)
  weighted by service criticality
```

Example:

| Service   | Score |
| --------- | ----- |
| Order     | 2.1   |
| Payment   | 3.8   |
| Inventory | 2.7   |

→ Domain score: **2.86 → 🟡 (at risk)**

